CatDescriptText: Mr. William Walters, mail clerk, 700 Webster Terrace, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that President Eisenhower should invoke the Taft-Hartley Act in steel strike?" answer reads: "I definitely do not think that it would be right. After the 80 day cooling-off period, there probably would be so much steel stockpiled, that the companies would not care whether work was resumed right away or not."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of William Walters wearing dark fedora, eyeglasses, and light colored zippered jacket, standing in front of Beck Shoes, Fifth Avenue,Downtown
